content.description: Looking at the crack, start with one hand in the triangle hold in the crack, and the other on a jug about three feet from the ground. Work your way up the arete with holds on both sides. The top is still mossy, so it can’t be topped. There is potential to top it, it just needs to be cleaned.
content.location: Once you’re at the top of the hill that you’ve climbed above the fence, work your way down to the river side above the falls. The rock face is about 10-15 feet upriver of the falls.

content.description: A small collection of rocks near a popular waterfall. Heavy traffic during weekends and summer.
